From Ed Green Pixel Cruncher Subject Re Well blow me yuk yuk yuk In article Robert D Castro writes When How do you decide that it is too windy to ride When it's too windy to When you're on the road in high winds stay Even more alert than your alert 'cause you're on a motorcycle and they're out to kill you kind of Be aware of the terrain and how it may funnel wind in sudden gusts well not gusts to somebody standing there but it's gusty 'cause you ride through it If you are riding in a steady crosswind be aware of a hill that will block the wind and adjust your lean Be aware of passing trucks to your windward side your lean angle will change dramatically both as you enter and as you leave their turbulance Reducing your profile may help ie lean on the gas tank and kiss the triple Keep a nimble hand on the steering be ready to countersteer into and out of sudden wind Keep a larger than usual buffer zone both ahead and behind and to the side you can easily be blown half a lane over before you can react by Keep a close eye on traffic in your mirror if someone is coming up wanting to pass get out of their way Stop often for short brakes extensive riding in high winds is both mentally and physically Ed Green former Ninjaite I was drinking last night with a biker and I showed him a picture of I said DoD Go on get to know her you'll like her The Grateful Dead It seemed like the least I could